Anyone stuck at making mario automatically become small again? I don't understand this code by Ania:

player.collides('mushroom', (m) => {
  player.biggify(7)
 destroy(m)
})

Supposedly this makes mario big for 7 seconds, but when did we define that time = 7 or time = the argument we are sending inside biggify? When biggify doesn't even have the timer inside it, it's inside big(). Completely lost here.
